# SKILL: ClearSky Presentation Engine
*Portable skill for generating branded ClearSky presentations via presentations-v3.html.*
*Tested on: tools.oga.earth/tools/presentations-v3.html · API: api-tools.oga.earth*

## Architecture
Single HTML file (1,168 lines). No build step. No framework.
Three output types generated client-side via pptxgenjs 3.12.0 from cdnjs.

## File locations
- Frontend: C:\brand-presentations\repos\oga-tools\tools\presentations-v3.html
- Worker endpoint: worker.js → POST /api/presentations/v2/generate
- Worker endpoint: worker.js → POST /api/presentations/v2/ingest-pds
- Live URL: https://tools.oga.earth/tools/presentations-v3.html
- API base: https://api-tools.oga.earth

## Three output types

### 1. Project Tearsheet (tearsheet)
3 pages, A4 portrait (8.27×11.69")
Fields: projectName, country, creditType, verraId, methodology, overview(500ch),
wccYear, wrcYear, totalCp1, jobsCreated, creditingPeriod, materialType,
output, vvb, sdgs(comma-separated), additionality(200ch), traceability(200ch),
impact(200ch), cobenefits[{title,desc}×4], contactName, contactEmail, contactPhone, counterparty

### 2. Presentation Deck (deck)
16:9 landscape (10×5.625")
Slides: Cover → Exec Summary → Market Context → Per-Project(×N) → Comparison → Contact
Fields: title, subtitle, summary(400ch), marketContext(400ch),
stats[{num,label}×4], projects[{name,country,type,metric,desc(250ch)}×3],
contactName, contactEmail, counterparty

### 3. White Paper (whitepaper)
A4 portrait. Section placeholders only — content edited in PowerPoint.
Fields: title, subtitle, sections[{header}×10]

## API endpoints

### POST /api/presentations/v2/generate
Generates AI brief from prompt + optional project context.
Request:
```json
{
  "prompt": "Build a deck for Shell targeting VM0047 ARR projects",
  "type": "deck",
  "project_ids": ["985", "1477"],
  "buyer_name": "Shell"
}
```
Response: JSON brief matching field schema above.
AI: Claude Sonnet via Anthropic API (ANTHROPIC_API_KEY worker secret).
Fallback: If API unavailable, frontend uses MOCK_PROJECTS data.
Timeout: 30s — wrap in try/catch (Standing Rule #28).

### POST /api/presentations/v2/ingest-pds
Ingests project document into knowledge base for context.
Request: FormData with file + project_id + owner='clearsky'
Response: {doc_id, word_count, status}

### GET /api/wiki/docs?type=project_dossier&owner=clearsky
Loads available project list for the project selector dropdown.
Response: {docs:[{id, title, project_id}]}
Fallback: var docs = MOCK_PROJECTS (line 660) — hardcoded fallback.

